{
  "stem": "21089.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Even if it was, as you say, let, let down the pens and no, either arrest them or shoot, or shot, and therefore the women could more pretend that if they have occasion, yeah, facility, and the conditions are right.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But with the men, there was no excuse, therefore, I had to be very careful.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Later.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the beginning, I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I knew what happened in the Jews because like when they had been going to Paneriai, which was-- they been shooting the Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was still I was in, when I was coming to Vilna, I knew what they were telling me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They'd been taking-- they'd take them from ghettos.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Even before the ghettos, they'd been taking Jews to Paneriai and later from-- which was ditches, they had been laid in the ditch and shot, a known fact.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I still remember, this was always early in the morning, they'd been walking.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You can see the walk and you knew that this is Jews on way to-- and this was not, not Germans, maybe one, two, three Germans with all Lithuanians in uniforms.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was still in Vilna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Vilna.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and this was always early in the morning not during the day, early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was on [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Mitskevitcha ?] Street where I was living.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] so, you know, there are many women, young women, and here is man from the city comes in, they want to make Anschluss, and I have to be very careful.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was always, no, I don't want to have anything to do with women.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
